    <title>Communication Pattern</title>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A communication pattern is a class functor which generates a graph. They are used to define the communication graph of a <ref refid="cage" kindref="compound">cage</ref>. GrayBat provides a handful of predefined pattern:</para><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><ref refid="structgraybat_1_1pattern_1_1FullyConnected" kindref="compound">graybat::pattern::FullyConnected</ref></para></listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="structgraybat_1_1pattern_1_1GridDiagonal" kindref="compound">graybat::pattern::GridDiagonal</ref></para></listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="structgraybat_1_1pattern_1_1Grid" kindref="compound">graybat::pattern::Grid</ref></para></listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="structgraybat_1_1pattern_1_1HyperCube" kindref="compound">graybat::pattern::HyperCube</ref></para></listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="structgraybat_1_1pattern_1_1InStar" kindref="compound">graybat::pattern::InStar</ref></para></listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="structgraybat_1_1pattern_1_1OutStar" kindref="compound">graybat::pattern::OutStar</ref></para></listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="structgraybat_1_1pattern_1_1BiStar" kindref="compound">graybat::pattern::BiStar</ref></para></listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="structgraybat_1_1pattern_1_1EdgeLess" kindref="compound">graybat::pattern::EdgeLess</ref></para></listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="structgraybat_1_1pattern_1_1Ring" kindref="compound">graybat::pattern::Ring</ref></para></listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="structgraybat_1_1pattern_1_1None" kindref="compound">graybat::pattern::None</ref></para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para><para>Own communication pattern can be build from the following pattern skeleton: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="keyword">namespace<sp/></highlight><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="namespacegraybat" kindref="compound">graybat</ref><sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">namespace<sp/></highlight><highlight class="normal">pattern<sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">struct<sp/></highlight><highlight class="normal">PatternSkeleton<sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>Functor<sp/>which<sp/>returns<sp/>a<sp/>desired<sp/>graph</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>GraphDescription<sp/>operator()(){</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>};</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/>}<sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">/*<sp/>pattern<sp/>*/</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">}<sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">/*<sp/>graybat<sp/>*/</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para><para><heading level="2">Further Links</heading>
</para><para><itemizedlist>
